		<td><b>Re: Possible to use this LCD to make a backlit Game Boy Colo</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, that's technically doable.<br /><br />Complicating factors:<br />* FPGA power consumption may be an issue<br />* Timing may be sufficiently incompatible such that it requires a framebuffer instead of a pair of linebuffers, requiring more RAM inside the FPGA and adding latency<br />* That screen is noticeably larger, which may require fiddly work to fit it into the case (and even more fiddly work to make it look good)<br />* I wouldn't personally pay that much money for that specific screen.<br />* - Alibaba is a wholesaler storefront, for people who want to buy hundreds (or more) of units. You might want aliexpress instead.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


